Please don't be insulted if I take a while to respond to comments. I probably just found myself needing another break from this site.

Various thoughts that still need revisions and/or re-evaluation (work in progress):

  1. Help people answering questions to spend their time more efficiently. By which I really mean stop answering questions in the comments, and accept answers that have helped. I often try to prioritize my time by looking through the unanswered questions list, but my effort is often foiled when I waste my time thinking about a question that turned out to have been answered in the comments.

  2. Help people asking questions. I've noticed some non-friendly behavior towards people writing answers by some who seem to be more interested in proving an answer wrong than making the answer right. Destructive criticism vs. constructive criticism. (Admittedly, some answers are not salvageable. But many are.) Try to understand what was meant instead of stopping your thoughts with "that's wrong".

  3. Make it OK to be wrong. I've seen some people justify answering questions in the comments with excuses along the lines of "I wasn't sure that was the answer." It should be OK for someone to propose an answer, then later retract it if it turns out to be off-base. Sometimes proposing a solution to try is more efficient than getting a clarification to determine if a solution is definitely the right one. (Asking for clarification should not be the same thing as asking if a certain solution works.) An incorrect answer based on incomplete information should not be considered a bad thing. For one thing, if the question is never clarified, it might be the correct answer for the next person to find the question.

Disclaimer: I write these as goals; I make no claim as to whether or not I personally achieve them.
